(14, 'Captain Hook', '&lt;p&gt;K&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;ids from 6 to 12 years old, pay 50% of the Adult price&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Kids from 13 years old and older, pay as an Adult&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Galleons of CAPTAIN HOOK Introducing..... THE BLACK PEARL!!!&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;In this Tour, youll get an experience full of magic and variety, reviving legends Pirates aboard the: Galleon I and Buccaneer II of CAPTAIN HOOK.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Staff and crew are fully outfitted in pirate costumes and cannons are fired on arrival and departure.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Throughout the cruise the pirates provide you an exciting telling of the history of Cancun, Isla Mujeres and the famous pirate MUNDAKA.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Following a delicious buffet or sit-down dinner, and while the host pirate CAPTAIN HOOK is entertaining the group with tales and illustrations of past pirate escapades, unbeknown to him another pirate ship is slowly approaching from the rear. Cloaked in total darkness, the sister ship El Galleon I, silently glides across the water pulling alongside Galleon II.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Suddenly CAPTAIN HOOK discovers the ship and shouts for his men to take position. The cannons are readied for attack.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;El Galleon I, Captained by the ruthless pirate MUNDAKA, attacks with cannons. His Pirates, armed with swords and pistols, sail from the masts landing on the decks of El Galleon II, intimidating the passengers and immediately taking CAPITAN HOOK captive.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;A sword fight ensues between the crew and pirates. The attack is enhanced with sound and light effect, and may involve group members or group leaders. Finally MUNDAKA&amp;acute;S pirates are captured, leaving him to fight alone.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;CAPTAIN HOOK is released and a fight takes place between HOOK and MUNDAKA. Finally HOOK is able to overcome MUNDAKA and subdue him.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Passengers involved deciding whether the body of MUNDAKA deserves to be thrown to the sharks or returned to isle Mujeres.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Once defeated the enemy CAPTAIN HOOK invites everyone to celebrate by ordering all pirates to continue with the music and dances along with artificial lights in this celebration of triumph and freedom.&lt;/p&gt;', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Show&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Music&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Dance&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Games&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Lifevests&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Beverage&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Dinner&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;', 'US$10 DOCK FEE SURCHARGE\r\nGround Transportation (please call us for ask a quotation)/Photos and Video\r\nSouvenirs/Tips', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Register at 6:30 pm&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;The Galleon leave at 07:00 pm&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Briefing and instructions&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Show&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Games&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Dinner&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Dance &amp;amp; Music&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Return to Cancun at 10:30 aprox.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', 'DAILY', '&lt;p&gt;Kids from 6 to 12 years old pay 50% of the Adult Price&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Kids from 13 year old and older pay as an Adult&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Three Choices for Dinner:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Caribbean lobster tail&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;New York Sirloin Strip&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Surf &amp;amp; Turf (Lobster and New York)&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Buffet: Salad Bar, Barbecued chicken, Vegetables, Rice, Bread, Dressing (Vinagrette, Thousand Island, Olive Oil), Desserts. accompanied by white or red wine.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Onboard Pirate entertainment (sword fiht presentation of Captain Hook and Contest.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Cruise the Night away on Cancun&amp;acute;s Bay.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Meeting Point: Maritime Terminal in Puerto