(44, 'Whaleshark', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Whale Shark is the largest fish that exists in the world today.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;It can grow to &lt;strong&gt;15 meters&lt;/strong&gt;. Whale Sharks &lt;strong&gt;prefer warm surface water &lt;/strong&gt;in those areas where colder water sprouts nutrient-rich, since these conditions favor the growth of plankton which they feed.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;One of the reasons why there are so many shale sharks in the waters of Holbox in summer.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;They are often seen shoals of mackerel and rays.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The whale shark han no features in common with whales except for its size and the fact that &lt;strong&gt;only eats tiny plankton &lt;/strong&gt;collected with the mouth open.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Usually feeds on the surface or slightly below this it feeds by filtering through their gills small plankton organisms in the water.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Whale Shark are viviparous &lt;/strong&gt;animals and sometimes sees young pup swimming with the elderly.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Whale Sharks &lt;strong&gt;are very docile and gentle&lt;/strong&gt;, not afraid when they are divers or swimmers approaching.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Due to weather the Whale Shark is only from May 22nd to September 17th.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guaranteeing&amp;nbsp; their Sighting of June 1st to August 31st.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Ground Transportation Round Trip (Hotel-Tour-Hotel)&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;During the Check in Coffe, juice and bread&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;boats&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;snorkel equipment&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;water and sodas&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;briefing and instructions&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;swim and sighting with the whale shark&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;on bord sandwiches (kitchen, tunny, ham and cheese)&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;ceviche after 45 minutes of snorkeling at coral reef.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;', ' P