(49, 'Coba Mayan Village', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cob&amp;aacute;&lt;/strong&gt; a magical place full of history.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Grat Pyramid &lt;strong&gt;Nohoch Mul &lt;/strong&gt;&quot;Large Hill&quot; is &lt;strong&gt;42mt. high&lt;/strong&gt;, this makes in the &lt;strong&gt;highest pyramyd in Yucatan Peninsula&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The five lakes of Coba are without a doubt the main reason why the Mayans settled here. &lt;br /&gt;Coba Lagoon, Riviera Maya, Mexico &lt;br /&gt;Coba reached its peak around 600 AD, yet it was mysteriously abandoned three hundred years later. Some archaeological evidence suggests that around the 8th century, when the population of the city was at its peak, it may have had as many as 55,000 residents.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Coba&#039;s buildings are connected by a complex network of sacbes, or stone roads, that are believed to have been built between 600 and 800 BC. There are over &lt;strong&gt;40 sacbes that cover approximately 100 km (63 miles). &lt;/strong&gt;The sacbes reach other important Mayan cities, like Yaxuna, near Chichen Itza, Pole, now called Xcaret, and the Muyil. They are believed to have been used by the military and for trading, and sacbes were also used for various rituals and pilgrimages.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;A/C Bus, Pick up and Drop off at Hotel&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Entrance at Ruins&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Tour guide&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Buffet&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Mayan community&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;', 'Drinks at the Restaurant/Bicycle /\r\nphoto and video / souvenirs/ Tips ', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Departure from Cancun 8:10am&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Arrival to Cob&amp;aacute; and visit the Archeological Zone 11:00am&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Departure from Cob&amp;aacute; 1:45pm&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Arrival to Piramides Restaurant 2:00pm&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Departure from Restaurant 2:45pm&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Arrival to The Mayan Community of Hidalgo 3:45pm&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Departure&amp;nbsp;from Mayan Community 3:45pm&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;arrival to Cancun&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;', 'MONDAY AND FRIDAY', '&lt;p&gt;On the Archeologic Zone the rate for use (video, camera) is USD$3.5&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Cannot use professional camera&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Bicycle $ 95 m.n (Optional)&lt;/p&gt;', '129.00', '99.00', NULL, NULL, 'coba-mayan-village', 1, 'images/pictures/4941111.gif', 1, NULL, '0', '1', 'Coba Mayan Village | coba tour | mayan village		', 'coba mayan village,tour mayan ruins,coba tour,mayan village,coba mayan ruins,mayan tour,mayan villages,coba ruins,mexican mayan ruins,coba mayan', 'COBA MAYAN VILLAGE; is a fun and interesting escursion that allows visitors to get to know and understand the REAL MEXICO in the mayan world.was found in 1994', '1'),
(50, 'Mayan Encounter Coba', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cob&amp;aacute; a magical place full of history.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Grat Pyramid &lt;strong&gt;Nohoch Mul &quot;Large Hill&quot; is 42mt. high&lt;/strong&gt;, this makes in the &lt;strong&gt;highest pyramyd in Yucatan Peninsula&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The five lakes of Coba are without a doubt the main reason why the Mayans settled here.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Coba Lagoon, Riviera Maya, Mexico&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Coba reached its peak around 600 AD, yet it was &lt;strong&gt;mysteriously abandoned three hundred years later&lt;/strong&gt;. Some archaeological evidence suggests that around the 8th century, when the population of the city was at its peak, it may have had as many as 55,000 residents.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Coba&#039;s buildings are &lt;strong&gt;connected by a complex network of sacbes&lt;/strong&gt;, or stone roads, that are believed to have been built between 600 and 800 BC. There are over 40 sacbes that cover approximately 100 km (63 miles). The sacbes reach other important &lt;strong&gt;Mayan cities&lt;/strong&gt;, like &lt;strong&gt;Yaxuna&lt;/strong&gt;, near &lt;strong&gt;Chichen Itza&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Pole&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;now called Xcaret&lt;/strong&gt;, and the &lt;strong&gt;Muyil&lt;/strong&gt;. They are believed to have been used by the &lt;strong&gt;military and for trading&lt;/strong&gt;, and sacbes were also used for various rituals and pilgrimages.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Discover Cob&amp;aacute;&amp;nbsp; the highest pyramid on the Yucatan Peninsula.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Travel into the forest and Maya communities where you will enjoy activities like &lt;strong&gt;rappel&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;zip-lining&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;strong&gt; cenote swimming&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;jungle walking &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;canoeing&lt;/strong&gt; on fresh water lagoons...&lt;/p&gt;', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;A/C Bus Pick uo and Drop off at Hotel&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Entrance at Ruins &lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Tour guide&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Buffet&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Mayan community&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', ' Sodas / Souvenirs / Photo and Video / Tips', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Pick up starts at 06:30 (depend your Hotel)&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Visit to Archeological Zone&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Walk through the jungle&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Rappel&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Swim at the Cenote&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Kayak&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Zip&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Mayan cemerony&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', 'MONDAY TO SATURDAY', '&lt;p&gt;Comfortable shoes and clothing for walk at the jungle, We recommend long sleeve shirt, tennis, hat, boots or sports sandals that strap on ankle, swim suit untherneath your clothes, towels and a dry set of clothes.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Biodegradable sunscreen, mosquito repellent, cash or credit card.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The tour is not suitable for people who suffer from physical disabilities or matrix, heart problems, pregnant women and people under the influence of alcohol or drugs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Maximum weight per person &lt;strong&gt;120 kg / 250 lbs&lt;/strong&gt;. Minimum age &lt;strong&gt;6 &lt;/strong&gt;years for activities&lt;/p&gt;', '139.00', '109.00', NULL, NULL, 'mayan-encounter-coba', 1, 'images/pictures/hk3ue54MINICTE.jpg', 1, NULL, '0', '1', 'Mayan Encounter Coba | mayan ruins tours | coba mayan Riviera			', 'mayan tour,mayan ruins tours,mexican ruins,coba mayan riviera,coba ruins tours,mayan temple tours,visit mayan ruins,tour mayan ruins,cancun activites.', 'Your unforgettable off-track adventure tour begins: exciting zip-line flying over an incredibly beautiful Cenote,and paddling on a lagoon of enormous beauty.', '1'),
(53, 'Tulum VIP Service', '&lt;p&gt;Tulum is located approximately &lt;strong&gt;south of Cancun&lt;/strong&gt;. At 1hr and 30min. from Cancun and 40min to Playa del Carmen. Not only is the largest coastal archaeological site in Mexico, is one of the corners of the &lt;strong&gt;Caribbean&lt;/strong&gt; where you can still enjoy the lush nature, and discover the interesting history of it.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Tulum means wall and is the name given this recently because the wall around the ruins&lt;/strong&gt;. It is believed that his original name was Zama, a word related to Zamal (dawn) &amp;nbsp;Here you can find: Culture, attraction, fun, tranquility and a lifetime experience&lt;/p&gt;', '&lt;p&gt;SUBURBAN 1-5 passengers&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Pick up at Hotel&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Entrance at Ruins&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;+USD$90 Tour guide&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;From Cancun&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;From Playa del Carmen&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Daily&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;LIMOUSINE 1-12 passengers&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Pick up at Hotel&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;+USD$90 Tour guide&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;From Cancun&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;From Playa del Carmen&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Availability&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;HELICOPTER 1-4 passengers&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Entrance at Ruins&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Tour guide&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;From Cancun&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Availability&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;PRIVATE PLANE 1-5 passengers&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Entrance at Ruins&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Tour guide&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;From Cancun&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Availability&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;', ' Suburban: Buffet\r\n\r\n Limousine:Entrance at Ruins\r\n\r\n Helicopter: Pick up at Hotel ', '&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;', 'DAILY / AVAILABILITY', '&lt;p&gt;Please Bring:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Comfortable shoes and clothing&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;biodegradable sunscreen&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;mosquito repellent&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Hat&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;swim suit&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;money for shopping&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;', '0.00', '0.00', NULL, NULL, 'tulum-vip-service', 31, 'images/pictures/5303254.gif', 1, '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;SUBURBAN USD$300 per unit&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;LIMOUSINE USD$492 per unit O/W +11% tax&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;HELICOPTER USD$2900 per unit From Cancun&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;PRIVATE PLANE USD$350 per person +11% tax + Airport tax From Cancun&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', '0', '3', 'Tulum VIP Service | mayan ruins trips | tulum ruins tour', 'mayan tulum,tulum attractions,tulum ruins beach,mayan ruins trips,mayan ruins of tulum tours,mayan ruins tulum tours,tulum mayan ruins tours,tulum ruins tour,visit tulum,tulum tours from cancun', 'Tulum not only is the largest coastal archaeological site in Mexico, is one of the corners of the Caribbean where you can still enjoy the lush nature. ', '1'),
(55, 'Chichen Itza Express', '&lt;p&gt;Chichen Itza Express is designed for tourists that would like to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;earlier to their hotels to assist an event or who do not wish to&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;make a full day trip.&lt;/p&gt;', '&lt;p&gt;*Boxed Breakfast&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;*Entrance to Archeological Zone&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', '*Stop Purchase handcrafts', '&lt;p&gt;Aproximately arrives to Chichen Itza at 10:45 where you have 2 hrs. in the archeological zone, of which you have&amp;nbsp;1 hr. is guided tour&amp;nbsp; and 1 hr. is free time&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;at 12:45 departure from Chichen Itza towards the Hotel Zone to arrive appoximately between 3:30PM and 4:00PM at the hotel lobby.&lt;/p&gt;', 'Tuesday and Thursday', '&lt;p&gt;Please take into account that we cannot guarantee a return&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;to the hotel before closing time of the lunch buffet for those&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;guests who are staying at an inclusive resort.&lt;/p&gt;', '79.00', '54.00', NULL, NULL, 'chichen-itza-express', 8, 'images/pictures/5595656.gif', 2, NULL, '0', '1', 'chichen-itza-express', NULL, NULL, '1'),
(56, 'Coba-Tankah', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COBA - TANKAH&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Cob&amp;aacute; a magical place full of history.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Great Pyramid &lt;strong&gt;Nohoch Mul &lt;/strong&gt;&quot;Large Hill&quot; is &lt;strong&gt;42mt. high&lt;/strong&gt;, this makes in the highest pyramyd in Yucatan Peninsula.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The five lakes of Coba are without a doubt the main reason why the Mayans settled here.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Coba Lagoon, Riviera Maya, Mexico&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Coba reached its peak around 600 AD, yet it was mysteriously abandoned three hundred years later.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Some archaeological evidence suggests that around the 8th century, when the population of the city was at its peak, it may have had as many as 55,000 residents.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Coba&#039;s buildings are connected by a complex network of sacbes, or stone roads, that are believed to have been built between 600 and 800 BC. There are over 40 sacbes that cover approximately 100 km (63 miles). The sacbes reach other important Mayan cities, like &lt;strong&gt;Yaxuna&lt;/strong&gt;, near &lt;strong&gt;Chichen Itza&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Pole&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;now called Xcaret&lt;/strong&gt;, and the &lt;strong&gt;Muyil&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;They are believed to have been used by the military and for trading, and sacbes were also used for various rituals and pilgrimages.&lt;/p&gt;', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;A/C Bus Pick up and Drop off at Hotel&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Entrance at Ruins&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Tou guide&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Typical Buffet&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', 'Sodas/ Souvenirs / Photo and Video Mayan Community / Tips', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;We arrive at Coba at 11am to start our 2hrs of guided tour of the area, with a guide who will assist the group all day long.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;After the guided tour of the archeological site, we will visit the &lt;strong&gt;cenote&amp;nbsp;tankah &lt;/strong&gt;where guests can &lt;strong&gt;swim for 30 minutes &lt;/strong&gt;enjoying a beautiful cave with stalactites and stalagmites (snorkeling is not available). Guests will have to shower before entering the sinkhole&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;After having enjoying a refreshing swim at the cenote, we head for&amp;nbsp;a local restaurat to enjoy a delicious &lt;strong&gt;lunch buffet &lt;/strong&gt;(salad, spaguetti, rice, beans, various stews) and desserts.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;', 'THURSDAY', '&lt;p&gt;Please Bring:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;comfortable walking shoes and clothe&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;biodegradable sunscreen&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;biodegradable repellant&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;camera&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;cash for shopping and Tips&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;', '109.00', '76.00', NULL, NULL, 'coba-cenote-and-aktunchen-underground-walks', 8, 'images/pictures/5676783.gif', 1, NULL, '0', '1', 'Coba, Cenote & Aktunchen |coba cenote aktunchen | coba ruins', 'coba ruins tours,mayan tours cancun,coba cancun,coba mayan ruins,excursion coba,grand cenote,coba cenote aktunchen,coba tours,tour coba,cancun coba', 'for those who enjoy the unknown world of Mayan Ruins of Coba can get acquainted and explore. And discover the perfect balance between the ruins and cenote', '1'),
(57, 'Tulum Xtreme', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Join us on the perfect combination of culture and adventure surrounded by the natural beauties of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Riviera Maya&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;. We will take you to the heart of the Maya land and the majestic archeological site of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tulum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;with its spectacular views over the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caribbean&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;waters. Experience the thrill of flying 20 m. ( 66 ft .) over the jungle canopy in the fastest zip-line circuit in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Riviera Maya&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;! We will prepare and gear you up to rappel 18 m. ( 60 ft.) intothe depths of a cenote. Swim and snorkel while exploring the astounding rock formations of a mystical Mayan underground river. A delicious typical Mexican lunch surrounded by the sounds of nature will await you at the end of your jungle adventure. Travel back in time and admire the beauty of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Aerial View of Tulum&quot; href=&quot;http://www.aventurasmayas.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Tulum-Xtreme-Tulum-From-Air.jpg&quot; rel=&quot;wp-prettyPhoto&quot;&gt;archeological site of Tulum&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt;, where a certified guide will make you feel part of history while you tour around this ceremonial center. Our guides will accompany you at all times sharing information regarding local traditions, flora and fauna, making sure you experience an&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;XTREME&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;day.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '&lt;p&gt;* Transportation in air-conditioned van&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;* Professional bilingual guide&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;* snorkeling &amp;amp; climing equipment&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;* Prescription mask available on request&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;* Lunch &amp;amp; beverages&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;* Insurance&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;* Taxes&lt;/p&gt;', '* Photos \r\n* Tips', '&lt;p&gt;Pick up lobby at 7:30&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;tour estimate time 6 hr&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', 'AVAILABLE', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Basic swimming skills required.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;This tour is not suitable for people with severe physical or motor handicap, serious heart problems, or people who are not able to handle moderate physical activity.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Children under the age of 6 may participate under the responsibility and direct supervision of a responsible parent or family member.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;People under the influence of alcohol or drugs will not be permitted to participate in this tour.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;div class=&quot;et-custom-list&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Comfortable clothes and footwear&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Water shoes&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Sunglasses and a hat&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Bathing suit&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Extra T-shirt and&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Towel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BIODEGRADABLE sunscreen and mosquito repellent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '0.00', '0.00', NULL, NULL, 'tulum-xtreme', 29, 'images/pictures/5764638.gif', 5, NULL, '0', '2', 'tulum xtreme', NULL, NULL, '1'),
(58, 'Chichen Itza Vip Service', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cultural Heritage of Yucatan, the Nation and mankind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Chich&amp;eacute;n Itz&amp;aacute;, was named one of &lt;strong&gt;THE NEW 7 WONDERS OF THE WORLD&lt;/strong&gt;, the most famous Mayan temple city, served as the political and economic center of the Mayan civilization. Its various structures - the &lt;strong&gt;pyramid of Kukulkan, the Temple of Chac Mool, the Hall of the Thousand Pillars, and the Playing Field of the Prisoners &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;ndash; can still be seen today and are demostrative of an extraordinary commitment to architectural space and composition.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The pyramid itself was the last, and arguably the greatest, of all &lt;strong&gt;Mayan temples&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUBURBAN 1-5 passengers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Pickup at the Hotel&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Entrance at the Ruins&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;+&lt;/strong&gt;90usd Tour guide&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;+&lt;/strong&gt;30usd per person Buffete&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;From Cancun and Playa del Carmen&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LIMOUSINE 1-12 passengers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Pickup at the Hotel&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Entrance Ruins&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;+&lt;/strong&gt;90usd Tour guide&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;+&lt;/strong&gt;30usd per person&amp;nbsp;Buffete&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;From Cancun and Playa del Carmen&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HELICOPTER 1-4 passengers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Entrance Ruins&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Tour guide&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Buffet&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;From Cancun and Playa del Carmen&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PRIVATE PLANE 1-5 passengers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\